         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>m<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w>t<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>r<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>l<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>k<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>nä</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>r</w><w>tmäṣ</w><w>tāmā</w><w>eṣäk</w><w>ku</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>tāpärk</w><w>nāñi</w><w>ka</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>agha</supplied>niṣṭabhavaṃ</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>räṣ</w><w>āñcālyi</w><w>tsaräny<supplied>o</supplied></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>m<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>a</w><w>ki</w><w>ñ<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>i</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w>säṃ</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... then over her ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... now my (f.) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the realm of the <hi>Aghaniṣṭa</hi> (<hi>Śuddhāvāsa</hi>) gods ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having ... with both hands put together ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a443"/>, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a445"/>, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a445a"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a445c"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a445e"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a445g"/>.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><distinct type="ms_text">– [l]·k·nä –\</distinct>: the reading of the <hi>l</hi> is particularly uncertain. On the assumption that the final part if a loc. in <hi>-aṃ</hi> followed by the emphatic particle <hi>-k</hi>, one might consider a reading <hi>(spa)l(t)k(a)nä(k)</hi> 'in zeal'.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>tāmā</hi>: between these two akṣaras one akṣara, obviously <hi>k·</hi>, has been wiped out, apparently deliberately. Ignoring this akṣara, the word division seems to have to be <hi>tmäṣ tāmā eṣäk</hi>. <hi>eṣäk</hi> may be construed with the perl. or the loc.; here the perlative of <hi>sām</hi> 'she' is used.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">: cf. <hi>aghaniṣṭabhavaṃ</hi> <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a265"/> a5.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>tsaräny(o)</hi>: This reading follows a suggestion of Ilya Itkin (p.c. 18 November 2015).</note></p>
         </div>
